Get-Command

Useful for: 

Discovering what PowerShell can do on your system  
Finding commands when you don’t know the exact name  
Confirming whether a module or cmdlet is installed  

Detailed Explanation 
PowerShell does not use traditional “commands” like CMD  
Instead, it uses cmdlets (verb-noun format)  
Get-Command shows everything PowerShell recognizes as executable  

Common Parameters 
-Name → Search for a specific command  
-Module → View commands from a specific module  
-CommandType → Filter by cmdlet, function, or alias


Get-Command -Name Get-*

Lists all commands starting with “Get”  
Shows command type and source module




